The '''2026 Chinese Grand Prix''' was a Formula One motor race.

== Background ==
Season context that should be skipped.

== Qualifying ==
Pierre Gasly qualified in the midfield. Alpine struggled for single-lap pace in sector two.

== Race ==
Max Verstappen retired on lap 45 with a coolant leak after a difficult race. Charles Leclerc was involved in a collision with George Russell on lap 57. A virtual safety car was deployed on lap 40, which helped Lewis Hamilton gain positions with a three-stop strategy.

